Do not touch frontend/.

Do not touch shared/ unless the task requires shared data or shared logic.

## Shared data / logic tasks

If the task affects shared data, learning logic, product logic, or business logic, update shared/ first.

Shared logic includes:

- language list
- language aliases
- flags/language icons
- i18n/localization
- niche list
- exam tracks
- level system
- lesson data
- vocabulary data
- grammar data
- kana/kanji data
- exercise data
- exercise builder logic
- answer checking logic
- accepted answers
- placement test
- daily goal
- heart/streak rules
- profile schema
- onboarding choices
- subscription plans
- AI quota rules

Do not create Flutter-only data that conflicts with Web.

If Flutter cannot directly consume shared JSON, mirror the same JSON into Flutter assets and document the sync.

## Shared data sync workflow

Any change affecting shared data or business logic must be made in `shared/` first.

Shared data includes:

- lesson data
- exercise logic
- language list
- native language list
- niche / learning focus list
- level system
- exam tracks
- onboarding options
- localization / i18n catalog
- placement policy
- auth provider catalog
- profile schema
- answer checking rules

Do not fix shared business logic only in Web or only in Flutter.

After changing JSON under `shared/config/` or `shared/i18n/`, run:

```powershell
npm run sync:flutter-assets
```

This copies shared JSON into `mobile/novalang_flutter/assets/shared/`.

If lesson/content generation is added later, run the future generate script before syncing Flutter assets.

Do not manually edit copied files under `mobile/novalang_flutter/assets/shared/` unless explicitly instructed. Update `shared/` and run the sync script instead.

UI-only changes may target only the specified platform.

Android-first design is allowed for mobile UI, but shared data must remain platform-independent.

## Localization rule

If uiLanguage = vi, all user-facing text must be Vietnamese.

Target learning language text stays in the learning language.

Example:

Japanese target:

こんにちは

Vietnamese UI/options:

xin chào
tạm biệt
cảm ơn
làm ơn

Do not show English UI/options when Vietnamese UI is selected.

## Exercise rules

Single-choice exercises must have:

- exactly 4 unique options when enough data exists
- exactly 1 correct answer
- no duplicate labels
- no duplicate values
- no distractor that is also correct

Match-pairs exercises must:

- check every pair exactly
- not mark correct just because a value was selected
- kana reading match must use kana → reading
- vocabulary meaning match must use vocabulary → meaning

Typed answers must:

- use acceptedAnswers
- normalize input before checking

Japanese TTS:

- use speechText when available
- do not send ambiguous kanji alone
- 雨（あめ） should speak あめ

## Android UI rules

NovaLang is Android-first.

Use mobile-first Flutter UI:

- SafeArea
- LayoutBuilder
- MediaQuery
- responsive spacing
- full-width cards on small screens
- visible back buttons
- bottom navigation with max 5 tabs
- no fixed phone width/height
- no layout designed only for one screen size

Do not use fixed page sizes like:

width: 390
height: 844

Small fixed icon sizes are okay.

